Serializes a `Tree` (from `crate::tree`) into the exact JSON shape `viz/index.html` expects to render: `{"categories": [...], "nodes": {...}}`. Entry point is `to_json(tree: &Tree) -> String`.

Hand-rolled string building, no `serde` — this is intentional per the crate's zero-runtime-deps invariant, and reuses `steno::json_string` for escaping rather than reimplementing it. Node fields written per entry: `terminal`, `multiLine`, `oneLiner`, `children`, `axis`, `description`, `oneLinerRoot`, `synthetic` — this exact key set and order is coupled to what `viz/index.html`'s JS expects; adding/renaming a `Node` field requires updating both `write_node` here and the JS consumer, with no compiler check tying them together.

Nodes are emitted in `tree.node_order` (first-seen order), not HashMap iteration order, so output is deterministic across runs. `write_opt_string`/`write_opt_axis` emit literal `null` for `None`, matching JS's expectations of nullable fields rather than omitting keys. `axis` serializes as `{"kind", "options": [{"label", "key"}]}` — the `Axis`/`Choice` struct shapes from `crate::axis` must stay aligned with this if those types change.